Out[5]:
<AxesSubplot:>
Graph 1.1.1 
Graph 1.1.1
In this heatmap, the loan_amount is highly correlated with installment and balance (0.93, 0.94) & paid_principal is related with paid_total (0.99). The reasons are as follows:
    1. For installment: installment is the total loan devided by terms (which is 60 or 36 months), so installment is roughly propotional to loan_amount.
    2. For balance: all the loans are made in 2018, which means the # of installments made is no more than 12. The balance is more than 2/3 or 5/6, which closes to the loan_amount.
    3. Paid_total is paid_principal*(1+interest_rate)

• Visualize the test results and propose enhancements to the model, what would you do if you had more time. Also describe assumptions you made and your approach.¶

The LinearSVC and poly-svc model I tried had a pretty poor behavior in classifying the the grades accurately. Because there are so many classes, the boundries are hard to detect.

  1. If more time given, I would try to use regression models to predict the interest rate values directly and assigning it to the closest interest rate level (corresponding sub_grade).
  2. Another method that i think would work is to perform CNN with more variables in a Multi-Layer Perceptron model. This method takes more time but could find more hidden principles.
